DESCRIPTION
Add etude gc to identify and prune unreachable, oversized, or externally referenced artifacts according to safe retention rules.

DESIGN
## Plan (gc semantics resolved: report + explicit safe prune; NO auto-collection)

**Storage model (grounded — determines what gc can collect).** Each run ref
(refs/etude/runs/<id>) is a commit whose tree holds manifest.json + ONLY the
blobs that manifest references — runmanifest.Writer.Write rejects any tree file
not in referencedArtifactPaths (ErrUnreferencedArtifact, manifest.go:237). So
"orphan blob within a ref tree" CANNOT exist by construction (out of scope).
Eval refs (refs/etude/evals/<id>) hold only eval_result.json and pin run
artifacts by ArtifactSource{RunID,Stage,Commit,Artifact}; the bytes live in the
run trees. Refs are the only roots. Cross-ref edges: eval ArtifactSource ->
run, and stage replay_of -> source run. Nothing references an eval. The gc UNIT
is the whole REF; git-object cleanup is delegated to `git gc` (etude gc never
touches the object DB).

**KEY DESIGN FINDING — there is NO automatic garbage in this store.** Orphan
blobs are impossible (Writer guard). A run ref with no inbound eval/replay edge
is a normal, deliberately-captured ROOT (the user's work), NOT garbage — so
auto-deleting "unreachable" runs would destroy captured data. Therefore v1 does
NOT auto-collect anything. `etude gc` is REPORT-by-default + EXPLICIT, safety-
checked targeted prune. (This is the honest semantics for a content-addressed
git-ref store; "automatic GC of unreachable artifacts" does not map onto it.)

**v1 behavior:**
- `etude gc [--max-size N]` (DEFAULT = report only, never deletes, exit 0):
  - TOTAL: total content-artifact bytes across all run refs (sum of
    ArtifactRef.Size for Storage==content), and ref counts (runs, evals).
  - OVERSIZED: run refs whose total content-artifact bytes exceed --max-size
    (when --max-size is given; omit the section otherwise), each with its size.
  - EXTERNAL: pointer artifacts (Storage==pointer) listed per run with their
    URIs — informational (v1 does NOT fetch/validate/delete external URIs).
- `etude gc --prune <run-id> [<run-id>...]` (EXPLICIT deletion of NAMED runs):
  - For each named run, enforce the SAFETY INVARIANT before deleting: REFUSE
    (skip + print why) if the run is pinned by any eval ArtifactSource.RunID OR
    is the replay_of.RunID source of any other run — deleting it would orphan a
    live eval target or replay link. Also refuse if the run id does not exist.
  - Delete the surviving named refs via refstore.DeleteRef
    (`git update-ref -d --no-deref refs/etude/runs/<id>`); print "pruned <id>".
    Unreferenced objects are left for `git gc` (mirrors refstore.go:91).
  - --prune with NO run-id args is an error ("--prune requires one or more run
    ids"). gc never deletes anything not explicitly named.
- Evals are never deletable by gc in v1 (no eval-prune); deferred.

**Safety invariant (must never break a reference).** Build the LIVE pin-set by
walking store.List("refs/etude/runs") + List("refs/etude/evals"): parse each
manifest.json + eval_result.json; pinnedRunIDs = {every eval Target/Context
ArtifactSource.RunID} ∪ {every stage ReplayOf.RunID}. A named run is prunable
ONLY if its id ∉ pinnedRunIDs (re-checked immediately before the delete). This
guarantees gc cannot orphan a live eval target or replay link.

